-- BP Performing Maintenance on Texas Refinery Through April 26
-- B y   M a r k   C h e d i a k
-- 2012-04-22T16:38:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/bp-performing-maintenance-on-texas-refinery-through-april-26.html
BP Plc (BP/)  said it will perform
maintenance at its Texas City refinery until April 26 after a
lightning strike caused a small fire at the plant yesterday.  BP will work on its ultracracker from today until 9 a.m.
local time on April 26, the company said in a  filing  with the
Texas Commission on Environmental Quality. The work may result
in flaring, according to the filing.  The company said yesterday that a hydrocracker at its
refinery was shut after lightning caused a fire at about 5 p.m.
local time. The fire was contained and there were no injuries,
the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Chediak in  San Francisco  at 
